<TITLE> Khaleda should face trial for letting Rajakar fly flag: Sajeda </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 23 (bdnews24.com)Senior Awami League leader Syeda Sajeda Chowdhury on Saturday said opposition leader Khaleda Zia should be put on trial for allowing perpetrators of war crimes to fly national flag in their cars. "Being the wife of a freedom fighter [Khaleda] let the Rajakar have national flag on their vehicles," Sajeda, also deputy leader of the parliament, said at a condolence meeting in the memory of metropolitan Mahila Awami League president Nilufar Kaiser in Chittagong Muslim Hall. "An anti-liberation force is still active to destroy us. It is time to put them on trial." The meeting was presided over by convener of condolence committee and vice chancellor of Chittagong University Dr Abu Yusuf Alam. Nilufar Kaiser, the wife of AL presidium leader Ataur Rahman Khan, died of cancer on Apr 6. bd
